# Thread-Safe Memory Allocator

A high-performance memory allocator implemented in C with segregated free lists, fine-grained locking, and per-thread caches for efficient concurrent allocation.

## Performance

Benchmarked on x86_64h:

| Configuration | Throughput | vs glibc malloc | Speedup vs Single-Threaded |
|---------------|-----------|-----------------|---------------------------|
| Single-threaded | 87M ops/sec | 0.52x | 1.0x |
| 2 threads | 86M ops/sec | 0.52x | 0.99x |
| 4 threads | 115M ops/sec | 0.70x | 1.32x |
| 8 threads | 144M ops/sec | 0.87x | 1.66x |



## Architecture

Each block contains:
- Header: Size (4B), allocation status (1B), free list pointer (4B)
- Footer: Size (4B), allocation status (1B) for backward coalescing

Size Class Distributions:
- Class 0: 1-8 words     (4-32 bytes)
- Class 1: 9-16 words    (36-64 bytes)
- Class 2: 17-32 words   (68-128 bytes)
- Class 3: 33-64 words   (132-256 bytes)
- Class 4: 65-128 words  (260-512 bytes)
- Class 5: 129-256 words (516-1024 bytes)
- Class 6: 257-512 words (1028-2048 bytes)
- Class 7: 513+ words    (2052+ bytes)


Thread-Local Caching: each thread maintains private caches (64 blocks per size class)

